Week 7 roundup: Around Northeast Florida high school football 
Sat, Oct 10, 2015 @ 12:15 am 
ELSEWHERE 
Queshaun Byrd’s early touchdown sparked Flagler Palm Coast (2-4) to a 17-8 win over host Palatka (2-4). ... Christ’s Church (5-2) lost its second straight game, falling 42-0 to visiting Orlando Christian Prep (7-0). ... Arlington Country Day (0-5) lost 37-0 to host Vernon (5-1). ... Bradford (4-3) spoiled the homecoming of Fernandina Beach (2-5) with a 32-18 win. ... Keystone Heights (4-2) defeated visiting Belleview 27-14. ... Potter’s House (3-3) lost 30-20 to visiting Jefferson County (4-2).
